    <fr:title text="A comonad for Grothendieck fibrations">A comonad for Grothendieck fibrations</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Reference</fr:taxon>
    <fr:meta name="doi">10.48550/arXiv.2305.01474</fr:meta>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>We study the 2-category theory of Grothendieck fibrations in the 2-category of functors <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbf {Cat}^{\to }]]></fr:tex>. After redrawing a few general results in that context, we show that fibrations over a given base are pseudo-coalgebras for a 2-comonad on  <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathbf {Cat}}_{/B}]]></fr:tex>. We use that result to explain how an arbitrary fibration is equivalent to one with a splitting.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
